ered hunger, thus her baby girl died. Punniyalakshmi, with her child Johnny into her arms, jumped into the sea. They were later saved by labourers and admitted at the hospital. There, Johnny ran away from his mother.\n\nMany years later, Johnny ([[C. Arunpandian]]) became a gangster in a port city. Johnny had met his mother but he still hated her and he preferred to maintain the distance between them. The police Inspector Alexander Veeramuthu (Georgi George) waited for the right moment to arrest Johnny. Johnny was the friend of the transsexual Gowri Kumar ([[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]]) who was Ethiraj's son. One night, Gowri Kumar killed a prostitute. Johnny was then wrongly accused with Gowri Kumar for killing the prostitute. At the court, Gowri Kumar was sentenced to life imprisonment, whereas Johnny got a seven-year prison sentence.\n\nSeven years later, Johnny is urged to take revenge on the public prosecutor Ramanujam ([[Poornam Vishwanathan]]). His first attempt to murder him fails. So he decides to spoil his daughter Rukkumani's ([[Shobana]]) life and he even stops her wedding. In the meantime, Johnny clashes with the smuggler Ethiraj. When Ethiraj's henchmen try to kill Johnny, his mother Punniyalakshmi intervenes and dies. Ethiraj then dies in a car accident. The fate leads Johnny to get married to Rukkumani. Rukkumani then changes him into a good person and Johnny starts to work as a labourer in the port. All goes well until Gowri Kumar gets released from jail. What transpires next forms the rest of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[C. Arunpandian]] as Johnny\n*[[Shobana]] as Rukkumani\n*[[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]] as Gowri Kumar\n*[[Alex (actor)|Alex]] as Ethiraj\n*[[Poornam Vishwanathan]] as Ramanujam\n*[[Charle]] as Jana\n*[[Jai Ganesh]] as Naamam (guest appearance)\n*[[Kavitha (actress)|Kavitha]] as Punniyalakshmi\n*Georgi George as Inspector Alexander Veeramuthu\n*[[K. R. Savithri]] as Mangalam, Rukkumani's mother\n*[[Disco Shanti]]\n*[[Anusha (actress)|Anusha]] as Radha, Rukkumani's father\n*[[Shakeela]]\n*[[M. R. Krishnamurthy]] as Narayanan\n*Manager Cheena as Doctor\n*Master Udaya Raj as Johnny (child)\n*[[Mahendran (actor)|Mahendran]] as Alexander Veeramuthu\n*Nellai Kabilan\n*Jayamani\n*Vincent Roy\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Thuraimugam\n| type       = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Adithyan]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1994\n| recorded   = 1994\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 28:38\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Adithyan]]\n| prev_title = [[Kizhakku Mugam]]\n| prev_year  = 1996\n| next_title = [[Roja Malare]]\n| next_year  = 1997\n}}\n\nThe film score and the soundtrack were composed by [[film composer]] [[Adithyan]]. The soundtrack, released in 1994, features 6 tracks with lyrics written by the film director [[K. Rajeshwar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://play.raaga.com/tamil/album/Thuraimugam-songs-T0004072|title=Thuraimugam Songs|accessdate=2016-11-07|publisher=play.raaga.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Thuraimugam-2010/ZNsHc63j9J0_|title=Thuraimugam Songs|accessdate=2016-11-07|publisher=saavn.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://groups.google.com/d/msg/soc.culture.tamil/VMl6yIi8sXs/NMkEiChKcsgJ|title=Ilaiyaraaja's recent compositions (was Re: May Madham)|date=1994-09-11|accessdate=2016-11-07|publisher=groups.google.com}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Track !! Song !! Singer(s) !! Duration\n|-\n|1 || 'Chinna Chinna' || [[K. S. Chithra]] || 5:32\n|-\n|2 || 'Rukkumani Wrongapora' || K. S. Chithra || 4:37\n|-\n|3 || 'Soda Bottle ' || [[Suresh Peters]], [[Adithyan]] || 5:46\n|-\n|4 || 'Yeanda Porandha' || M. G. Sundar || 4:21