ited Kingdom general election|General election 1929]]: Neath<ref name=\"Craig, F. W. S. 1918-45\"/>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[William Jenkins (Labour politician)|William Jenkins]]\n  |votes      = 29,455\n  |percentage = 60.2\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Jack Jones (novelist)|Jack Jones]]\n  |votes      = 14,554\n  |percentage = 29.8\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Unionist Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = David J. Evans\n  |votes      = 4,892\n  |percentage = 10.0\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 14,901\n  |percentage = 30.4\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 48,901\n  |percentage = 82.1\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 48,901\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Labour Party (UK)\n  |swing      = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1924 United Kingdom general election|General election 1924]]: Neath<ref name=\"Craig, F. W. S. 1918-45\"/>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate unopposed with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[William Jenkins (Labour politician)|William Jenkins]]\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 46,996\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link no swing|\n  |winner     = Labour Party (UK)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin|title=[[1923 United Kingdom general election|General election 1923]]: Neath<ref name=\"Craig, F. W. S. 1918-45\"/>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[William Jenkins (Labour politician)|William Jenkins]]\n  |votes      = 20,764\n  |percentage = 62.3\n  |change     = +2.8\n}}\n{{Election box